external_knowledge:
- "Type of visit" refers to the category of the visit, for example, routine check-up, emergency, etc.;
- "Documents attached to the visit" refers to any files or notes related to the visit;
- "Rating given by the patient" is the numerical score (1-5) provided by the patient regarding the service quality;
- "Concluded" means the visit has been marked as completed.

sql:
SELECT visits.diagnosis, users.name
FROM visits
INNER JOIN users ON visits.doctor_id = users.user_id;

SELECT visit_id, note
FROM visit_notes
WHERE note LIKE '%concerns%';

SELECT visit_id, code_type
FROM visit_codes
WHERE code = 'XA-1204110';

SELECT AVG(Number_of_Visits) AS Average_Number_of_Visits
FROM (
  SELECT medical_center_id, COUNT(*) AS Number_of_Visits
  FROM visits
  GROUP BY medical_center_id
);

SELECT AVG(julianday(next_appointment_date) - julianday(visit_date_time)) AS average_visit_duration
FROM visits
WHERE julianday(next_appointment_date) - julianday(visit_date_time) > 30;

SELECT DISTINCT p.name AS patient_name
FROM patients p
JOIN visits v ON p.patient_id = v.patient_id;

SELECT name 
FROM patients 
WHERE patient_id NOT IN (SELECT patient_id FROM visits);

SELECT DISTINCT payors.name
FROM visits
INNER JOIN payors ON visits.payor_id = payors.payor_id;

external_knowledge:
- NPS score of 9 represents a high level of patient satisfaction; 
- 'Flu' refers to visits related to influenza treatment or diagnosis; 
- "Planting a seed of satisfaction" is a metaphor for giving positive feedback;
- "Gardeners of goodwill" refers to patients who provide positive reviews;
- "Soil of their feedback" metaphorically represents the content of their feedback;
- "Starlight of their ratings" is a poetic way of referring to the star ratings given by the patients.
